The defendant Freddie Lewis Teamer Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Heroin(>3-10g) [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(d)2.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION 2YEARS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
- Court ordered defendant to serve 1 YEAR CONDITION TIME in the House of Correction without goodtime credit; release for The Day Reporting Center, work and inmate work assignments. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. FORTHWITH

- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.

- Regularly participate in an HSED or GED program until completed. 
- Seek/Maintain fulltime employment.
- Defendant to not associate with any known gang member, associate or affiliate. 
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with all child support court orders.
- Complete Parenting or Fatherhood course.

- Fine is set at ZERO.

- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, due no later than 12-31-2016. Any remaining balance will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.
